"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-07-25-paris-olympics-summer-games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"After months of anticipation, the2024 Summer Olympics Gamesare nearly underway.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 79, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beginning on Friday, July 26 in Paris, France, this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympics mark a return to normalcy.\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 112, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 119, \"end\": 125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999976753315, \"rank\": 2.2644203464820203e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Postponed to 2021 due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the 2020 Tokyo Olympics were framed by stringent public health guidelines that barred spectators from attending.\", \"from\": 177, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999999997507985, \"rank\": 2.4880862274064536e-10, \"text\": \"COVID-19 pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2022 Winter Olympics in Beijing took place under similar restrictions.\\u00c2  Now, Paris has become the second city ever (after London) to host the Olympics three times, having previously served as the venue in 1900 and 1924.\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 366, \"end\": 373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9921682435391483, \"rank\": 0.007893081024408204, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.012497452527297e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last century has seen notable changes.\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1924,only 3,089 athletes(and only 135 women) participated in the Games, compared to this year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sizeable roster of 10,500 competitors evenly split among the sexes participating in 32 different sports.\\u00c2  Related  If you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re based in the U.S., you can tune in to the Olympics on cable TV networks (NBC, USA, Golf Channel, CNBC, and E!)\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.6648516935594136, \"rank\": 0.5040791323509435, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999810412215121, \"rank\": 1.895913778638348e-05, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golf_Channel\", \"score\": 0.99999687241723, \"rank\": 3.1275922319796675e-06, \"text\": \"Golf Channel\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golf_Channel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golf_Channel\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8890178876383948e-16, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"or streaming services like Peacock, NBCOlympics.com, NBC.com, the NBC App or the NBC Olympics App.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 973, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4274741352968998e-23, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 999, \"end\": 1006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC.com\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From varied venues in and around Paris to key Team USA athletes to follow, check out Salon\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s list of everything you should know about this summer's Olympic Games before you tune in.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9079136523269187e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in the history of the Olympic Summer Games, the Opening Ceremony will take place outside of a stadium.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999992342055, \"rank\": 7.512599720063169e-10, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the ceremony will be waterborne across nearly four miles of Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 famous Seine River, ushering in athletes on a parade of boats designated to reflect each respective country.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to theOlympics' official website,the boats will be fitted with cameras to provide fans watching online and via television with a close-up view of the athletes.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  Starting at 7:30 p.m. CET (10:30 a.m. PST and 1:30 p.m. EST), the procession will depart from the Austerlitz Bridge near the Jardin des Plantes and will end in front of the Trocad\\u00c3\\u00a9ro Gardens, where the remaining elements of the ceremony will unfold.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austerlitz Bridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  SuperstarsCeline DionandLady Gagaare reportedly slated to perform aduetrendition of\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00c3\\u0089dith Piaf\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s \\\"La Vie en Rose\\\" at the opening ceremony, marking Dion's first public performance since she was forced to stop touring after revealing to the world that she had been diagnosed with Stiff Person Syndrome (SPS), a rare autoimmune neurological disorder.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  The Paris 2024 Opening Ceremony will be the largest in Olympic history, as noted by the official site.\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9996636974192467, \"rank\": 0.0003363673518471088, \"text\": \"SPS\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With 80 super-sized screens and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cstrategically placed speakers,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d it will also be accessible.\\u00c2  This year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic mascots are the Phryge and the Paralympic Phryge, small creatures that resemble a Phrygian cap, a slightly drooping, cone-shaped hat typically associated with themes of liberty in European and colonial cultures.Per the Olympic website,Phrygian caps \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009care a common reference for French people, including in the world of art (as a metaphor for freedom) and as a symbol of the Republic in French institutions .\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phrygian cap\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 2786, \"end\": 2794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 0.99999999931606, \"rank\": 6.836283492652654e-10, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 2830, \"end\": 2843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2938, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995486374495607, \"rank\": 0.0004486035460860362, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \".\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are also an international symbol of liberty worn by freed slaves in Roman times and appearing on different emblems in North and South America.\", \"from\": 2964, \"to\": 3111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.7744612086169353, \"rank\": 0.14745738154448723, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 3097, \"end\": 3110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_America\", \"score\": 0.9999934509756522, \"rank\": 6.549067009884858e-06, \"text\": \"South America\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_America\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAs Paris 2024\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s vision is to demonstrate that sport can change lives, the mascots will be playing a major role by leading a revelation through sport,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d the site adds.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  The Phryges are red, white and blue to reflect France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tri-colored flag and wear the gold Paris 2024 logo \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 including the Olympic symbol of five interlaced rings \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 on their chests.\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3387, \"end\": 3397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.60218052546064e-35, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The motto of the Olympic Phryges is \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAlone we go faster, but together we go further,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d echoing a sense of global solidarity.\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking, otherwise known asbreakdancing,will make its inaugural entrance to the Olympic stage in Paris.\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3709, \"end\": 3714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With roots in New York\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Bronx borough during the 1980s, breaking is the only new sport to be added to the rotation of events.\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Asreported by The Washington Post,there will be two breaking events \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 one for men and one for women \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 over two days with 16 dancers (known as B-Boys and B-Girls) taking part in each session.\\u00c2  \\u00c2  Per NBC,a panel of nine judges will evaluate the dancers based oncreativity, personality, technique, variety, performativity and musicality.\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 4185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3859, \"end\": 3878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1409480714658307e-24, \"text\": \"The Washington Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Washington_Post\"}, {\"begin\": 4049, \"end\": 4052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.6648516935594136, \"rank\": 0.5040791323509435, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The dancers are unaware of what music will be played during their routine and must improvise their performance.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00c2Breaking made its debut at the 2018 Youth Olympic Games in Buenos Aires before being selected for Paris.\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4359, \"end\": 4371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\", \"score\": 0.9999999985793693, \"rank\": 1.4201461898779146e-09, \"text\": \"Buenos Aires\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\"}, {\"begin\": 4398, \"end\": 4403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will not return for the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles, according to NBC.\\u00c2Four of the sports that were introduced during the Tokyo Olympics \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 including 3\\u00c3\\u00973 basketball, surfing, sport climbing and skateboarding \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 will make a reappearance this summer.\", \"from\": 4405, \"to\": 4660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4449, \"end\": 4460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.65232556099783e-13, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the height of the Olympic action \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and some of the most popular events, like swimming and gymnastics \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 will transpire in central Paris, many other sports will take further afield.\", \"from\": 4662, \"to\": 4851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4801, \"end\": 4806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Roucas-Blanc Marina in the coastal city of Marseille, located in the south of France, will serve as a home base for the sailing competition.\\u00c2According to the Olympic website,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthe quality of the water conditions off the coast of Marseille, with relatively constant winds and a coastal configuration that is correctly oriented in relation to the dominant winds, without any currents or tides, will ensure ideal tactical and strategic conditions for the competitors.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00c2  Soccer matches will also be held in Marseille at the Stade V\\u00c3\\u00a9lodrome arena and at various stadiums in Bordeaux, Saint-\\u00c3\\u0089tienne, Lyon, Nantes and Nice,as noted by CNN  The surfing competition will not even take place in the same hemisphere.\", \"from\": 4852, \"to\": 5569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4899, \"end\": 4908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.999999999659849, \"rank\": 3.3983105184020687e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 4934, \"end\": 4940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999976753315, \"rank\": 2.2644203464820203e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5086, \"end\": 5095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.999999999659849, \"rank\": 3.3983105184020687e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 5365, \"end\": 5374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.999999999659849, \"rank\": 3.3983105184020687e-10, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 5432, \"end\": 5440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"score\": 0.9999999999517968, \"rank\": 4.803070118414597e-11, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\"}, {\"begin\": 5458, \"end\": 5462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.427047230309096e-13, \"text\": \"Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyon\"}, {\"begin\": 5464, \"end\": 5470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nantes\", \"score\": 0.9999999994624886, \"rank\": 5.373106116315552e-10, \"text\": \"Nantes\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nantes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nantes\"}, {\"begin\": 5475, \"end\": 5479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5118267147029e-13, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}, {\"begin\": 5492, \"end\": 5495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999999998926796, \"rank\": 1.0739987578448688e-10, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead surf's up in Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o, a village off the southeastern coast of Tahiti in French Polynesia in the middle of the Pacific Ocean.\", \"from\": 5570, \"to\": 5706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5644, \"end\": 5650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999969832233576, \"rank\": 3.0167859506613004e-06, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 9,800 miles away from Paris, Teahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o is the most distant venue from a host city in Games\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 history,according to Washington Post.\", \"from\": 5707, \"to\": 5843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5732, \"end\": 5737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5827, \"end\": 5837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9992706505647289, \"rank\": 0.0007298752584681685, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  Known as\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe End of the Road,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dTeahupo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099o is infamous for its idyllic surfing conditions, notoriously heavy waves and shallow shelf of coral, making it a deeply challenging surf venue.\", \"from\": 5845, \"to\": 6036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) elected to keep the majority of Russian and Belarusian athletes off the Paris ticket, a decision stemming from the Kremlin\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s ongoingwar in Ukraine.\", \"from\": 6038, \"to\": 6229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6042, \"end\": 6079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6112, \"end\": 6119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.783214800282512, \"rank\": 0.27673898975891587, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 6124, \"end\": 6134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9999999895508154, \"rank\": 7.250401252182513e-09, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}, {\"begin\": 6152, \"end\": 6157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6221, \"end\": 6228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.999999951955034, \"rank\": 3.828520264782559e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  Eligible \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and formally invited \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 Russian and Belarusian athletes will be permitted to compete asIndividual Neutral Athletes,\\u00c2\\u00a0or AINs.Per USA Today,the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAIN classification means that Russian and Belarusian flags, national anthems and uniforms will be absent from the Paris Games.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00c2  Instead, these athletes will compete under a designated green flag.\", \"from\": 6231, \"to\": 6595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6272, \"end\": 6279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.783214800282512, \"rank\": 0.27673898975891587, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 6284, \"end\": 6294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9999999895508154, \"rank\": 7.250401252182513e-09, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}, {\"begin\": 6424, \"end\": 6431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.783214800282512, \"rank\": 0.27673898975891587, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 6436, \"end\": 6446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"score\": 0.9999999895508154, \"rank\": 7.250401252182513e-09, \"text\": \"Belarusian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarus\"}, {\"begin\": 6508, \"end\": 6513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of appearing in Paris, they were mandated to prove that they do not support Russia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s invasion of Ukraine and had never served in the Russian or Belarusian armed forces.\", \"from\": 6596, \"to\": 6772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6618, \"end\": 6623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.249754493796806e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6701, \"end\": 6708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.999999951955034, \"rank\": 3.828520264782559e-08, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 6737, \"end\": 6744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.783214800282512, \"rank\": 0.27673898975891587, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 6748, \"end\": 6771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armed_Forces_of_Belarus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Belarusian armed forces\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armed_Forces_of_Belarus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armed_Forces_of_Belarus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the IOC, \\\"Participation in the Olympic Games Paris 2024 is subject to the athlete\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s acceptance of the individual invitation and signature of the Conditions of Participation applicable to all participants.\", \"from\": 6773, \"to\": 6992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6790, \"end\": 6793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0521982543513966e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The form contains a commitment to respect the Olympic Charter, including 'the peace mission of the Olympic Movement.'\\\"\", \"from\": 6993, \"to\": 7111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7092, \"end\": 7108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999935062078, \"rank\": 6.4941719730289435e-09, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2  \\\"The Olympic Movement is united in its sense of fairness not to punish athletes for the decisions of their government if they are not actively participating in them,\\\" the IOC said in February of 2022, around the time Russia launched its invasion.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\\"We are committed to fair competitions for everybody without any discrimination.\\\"\", \"from\": 7113, \"to\": 7445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7121, \"end\": 7137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999935062078, \"rank\": 6.4941719730289435e-09, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 7287, \"end\": 7290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0521982543513966e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re